{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01C1VE9SXijSJdjgyngcGVMe","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the codebase. This is a Jakarta EE 10 application with:\n- JPA entities, DAOs, Services\n- JAX-RS REST endpoints (under `/rest` path) \n- JSF (PrimeFaces) views\n- EJB stateless beans\n- Liberty server runtime\n\nThe migration strategy for Quarkus:\n1. Replace EJB `@Stateless` with CDI `@ApplicationScoped` + `@Transactional`\n2. Replace `@EJB` with `@Inject`\n3. Keep JPA entities mostly the same (Quarkus supports Hibernate ORM)\n4. Keep JAX-RS endpoints (Quarkus uses RESTEasy)\n5. Remove JSF/PrimeFaces views (not supported in Quarkus) - keep REST API\n6. Replace Liberty persistence.xml with Quarkus application.properties\n7. Use Quarkus Jackson instead of JSON-B/JAXB for serialization\n\nLet me now create the entire migrated application. I'll start with the smoke test and new pom.xml:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7992,"cache_read_input_tokens":81112,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":7992,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":778},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"faf55576-b919-4f0c-9954-ff7c05fa2fb1","uuid":"6e916247-f1bb-43b1-8e9c-7e81a8edcc5f"}
